{
  "stem": "11998.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My three daughters with their husbands and my wife and I, we went and we had an odyssey back to my birthplace, to where I spend the-- where I was at first at Sosnoviec, then the open ghetto in Sosnoviec, and then to Srodula.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then, we went from there-- we to Auschwitz to complete the path.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I must say, it was a-- it was a victorious trip.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was a trip to remember the bad things, but also to appreciate what we have now, the fact that I've been able to re-establish-- establish a family, and have eight grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they go to day school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we live a Jewish life, something that Hitler didn't want us to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "When Hitler gave me a ticket to Auschwitz, it was a one-way ticket.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I came back, as it were, victorious, after almost being defeated.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was an apartment building.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's a courtyard, and we lived on the ground floor, which is-- we had very unpretentious dwelling place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It consists of one bedroom and a kitchen, which was our living room and dining room.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in the bedroom, we made room for Pesach to have a Seder.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a dining room table in the-- in the bedroom, where we had our Pesach Seder.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you were saying what languages I was talking.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So when I was on the street, I spoke German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When I spoke to my parents, they spoke to me Yiddish, and I spoke to them either in German or in Polish.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then, when I went to school, of course, I had to learn Polish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, in addition to that, there was a Silesian jargon which we always used to talk on the street, as well.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
